			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<br><blockquote><hr>Grumbuk-Dev wrote:<br>I think that having this change ignored if the bard isn't at the top of the NPC's hate list is a good suggestion and we'll consider it today before we make final code changes. Right now that seems like a good way to retain almost all of the group/raid benefits of these songs while narrowing the focus of the fix even more tightly on what we are trying to acheive, but I can't promise anything because the designers might show me something I'm overlooking.<br><br>To answer a few questions though:<br><br>- When the damage component is ignored, the rest of the spell effects will remain. <br>- No there won't be any "compensation" for this change. We consider it something that has been overpowered and broken for far too long. We would have liked to have fixed this sooner but we've had other priorities. <br>- If the mob is rooted and trying to move, then the dot will not be applied. As mentioned above, we're going to discuss having this be less restrictive and have it only apply to when the NPC is trying to reach the bard but I can't promise that yet.<br>- Yes soloing will be harder for bards who liked to PBAE kite. This is one of the many goals of this change because we believe its current state is unbalanced. Not only is it the exp that is unbalanced, it is the huge amount of loot people gain from doing it. Note that these are only a couple of the many reasons we are making this change.<p>Message Edited by Grumbuk-Dev on <span class=date_text>09-08-2004</span> <span class=time_text>08:42 AM</span><br><hr></blockquote><br><br><br>Will the effect be canceled if the MOB has a movement capability of 0? (i.e. he is snared and trying to death walk away, or it's rooted?)
