			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Unfortunately, this will continue to affect lower level bards, I remember when meleeing orcs and my 2 point per tick chords of dissonance did WAY more damage than my own horrible sword swinging. I thought there was a REASON we got our first AE damage song at level 2, now we have to wait till level 12 for Bellows for our first one, maybe a low level kick would help compensate those poor bards who just can't kill the mob before their health runs out.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>More Important to me personally, is how it affects the possibilities for bards who group together. I regularly group with other bards, and because cod, coc/mom stack by unlimited numbers, this was a way for us to find some reasonable dps while grouped together against a meleeing or feared mob.&nbsp; It will still be possible for bards to work together in a team, but it is sad to see this creative song lineup taken away.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>P.S. This sounds difficult, but I have seen there is no reason to be guessing what is programmable and what is not......AE works as it has previously if the mobs con green to the bard (for farming), and in the new way if not green.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I really love bards, but ongoing and escalating discouragement give me less hope every day for what lies at the end of the road for us, is there anything to look forward to, that we can be tempted with a bit of excitement for?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
