						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>I can get an AA every&nbsp;25 minutes in Plane of Fire easily.&nbsp; With TDoK it doesn't take too much longer, but having maxed percussion mod helps.&nbsp; I don't think that's too unreasonable of an experience gain.&nbsp; Not flagged for fire?&nbsp; You can get an AA every 45 minutes to an hour soloing Halls of Honor then.&nbsp; If you're flagged for Kod'taz, the experience is equivalent (actually slightly better) in both Kod'taz and Yxtta if you're soloing.&nbsp; The only problem you have to deal with in those cases is mobs that summon.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm a 65 bard, Time and GoD geared, and I never have AE kited for experience.&nbsp; I find it boring and don't have&nbsp;a computer which can handle the lag of pulling 20+ mobs in tow behind me without having a spike and getting mauled.&nbsp; I've gotten over 300 AA's in the last 2 months doing nothing but groups and chant kiting.&nbsp; I swarm kite Nightmare and Disease when no one is around, but that gets extremely boring after a while.&nbsp; With Omens swarm kiting will more or less be faded out, but I'm perfectly fine chant kiting stuff down when I need to solo.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>All of that being said, I really don't agree with some ways this change is being implemented in.&nbsp; When I'm doing faction work or helping raids in&nbsp;a lower level setting (i.e. Chardok royals, etc), I almost always pull out my PBAE's.&nbsp; When I'm doing solo camps I almost always have at least one of my PBAE's (usually MoM) loaded for emergency reasons when I need to slow all the mobs that are pounding away on me.&nbsp; I also use my PBAE's in an attempt to pull aggro off folks, though not really in the higher level zones that often.&nbsp; If this change were to go through with me being the top of the aggro, I would be struggling to hold aggro using my AE songs.&nbsp; I really don't like the idea of that <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-sad.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm also disliking the idea that moving at all while using these AE's decreases the range to a useless amount, but hopefully the resulting range will be enough to hit stuff that is within range and meleeing me.&nbsp; If that's the case I have no problems with the change, but please don't change it so that the damage doesn't take effect if I'm top of the aggro list or ONLY one on the aggro--I do twist PBAE's while solo meleeing multiple mobs so that would kill my use for doing that.</DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
