Grumbuk-Dev wrote:<BR>- No there won't be any "compensation" for this change. We consider it something that has been overpowered and broken for far too long. We would have liked to have fixed this sooner but we've had other priorities. <BR><BR>- Yes soloing will be harder for bards who liked to PBAE kite. This is one of the many goals of this change because we believe its current state is unbalanced. Not only is it the exp that is unbalanced, it is the huge amount of loot people gain from doing it. Note that these are only a couple of the many reasons we are making this change. 
<HR>

<P></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Grumbuk, your responses are really appreciated, as many here have noted.</P>
<P>But to the above points - removing&nbsp;<STRONG>legit </STRONG>AE kite soloing - this is the concern to the players.&nbsp; And there hasn't been any differentiation on your part between the legitimate and exploitatative uses of this way of soloing.&nbsp; It's clear that bards who are 65+ enjoy having this method of solo play to use for the acceptable number of npc's, and that it's the only way to gain solo exp that is competitive&nbsp;with other solo classes at that level.&nbsp; If there isn't even the faintest hint of a desire to someday, somehow&nbsp;have the proper hours allocated to correctly fixing this exploit while letting the class retain its ability, or returning it somehow, I really fail to understand where the no-compensation mindset comes from.&nbsp; If some people exploited the use of root would you take root away from druids and not somehow compensate them?&nbsp; I understand that it's difficult to see the importance of the legitimate use of this&nbsp; solo technique, but the whole point that people are making is that this is really the only solo option left to them by that point in the game - and that it is very balanced when used in those situations.&nbsp; If OoW would make this kind of kiting insanely powerful, then don't high-level bards deserve another way to solo instead...or something??&nbsp; I mean bard players have been helping pay SOE to create the content in OoW, and their reward for paying every month is new content that forces them to be stripped of an entire style of class gameplay?&nbsp; Sounds just wrong.</P></DIV></DIV>
																		
