			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 254 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_3.gif' border=0 alt='4 ratings - 3.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<FONT color=#ffffff></FONT><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV><EM><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT></EM></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>Make Targeted AEs follow the same rules,&nbsp; Make charming extremely more difficult for chanters, and figure out a way to nerf necros.&nbsp; Charming is overpowered, Quad kiting is overpowered, snare/dot kiting is overpowered.&nbsp; The reason you guys haven't touched AE kiting in so long is because you will now have to balance all of the rest of these exploits.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffffff>Lets see, targeted ae's have a limit of 4 targets.&nbsp; Charm is overpowered, but the level of risk and chance for abuse pale in comparison to PBAE DoT&nbsp;kiting.&nbsp; Snare/DoT kiting? Please stop grasping at straws...</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT></DIV></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>-You say the exp is unbalanced.&nbsp; There are several classes that can make as good if not substantially better exp than AE kiting bards.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffffff>Bull.&nbsp; I challenge you to come up with one example where this is true.&nbsp; After seeing bards AE kite the second field in PoFire for hours and hours, making around 5-6aa per hour (I'm not joking).&nbsp; I also challenge you to provide me with a situation when you can actually find a necro/chanter soloing 5 aa per hour.&nbsp; That just doesn't happen... anywhere.&nbsp; The best you can manage is around 2-2.5 per hour if you are very lucky.&nbsp; KT groups make around that same amount, so it isn't even worth soloing.&nbsp; Quadding is far more difficult in vxed or tipt than you think.&nbsp; Summoning mobs are quite frequent, and it only takes one of those to ruin your day.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffffff>In short, stop the hyperbole and grow up.&nbsp; We all know PBAE dot kiting was ridiculously overpowered and should have been nerfed ages ago.&nbsp; I think this change is a bit extreme, but given how exploitable this was, I see no alternative.&nbsp; Yes, it sucks for those that legitimately ae kited.&nbsp; However, those that did ae kite should realize how overpowered it was.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffffff>I congratulate the developers for finally tackling this issue, irrespective of the uproar.&nbsp; If only they would have done this on more issues in the past.</FONT></DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV></DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
